When I was around seventh grade I was addicted to reading 4chan greentext screencaps on my PC but when I was at my village with like 0.07 mbps internet it would take ~15 minutes for a screencap to fully load. I also once torrented Counter-Strike: Condition Zero over like one week

Bertrand Russell was right that mankind will eventually split into two fully separate races, normies are already separating, if you look at the For You Page the stuff they are discussing there, the way they talk, it has nothing in common with us now. They are simply molting away.

I would open a greentext screencap in a new tab and just leave for a walk or do something else while it was loading. Most people never get to experience the internet at those speeds. It's like leaving a bucket of water to fill up at the sink or something physical like that.

Like the concept of going to an isolated village and everyone looks sort of weird and "off" there with fishy eyes and thick skin and everyone moves slowly and talks crudely around town. Clinically hypothyroid people from 19th century iodine deficient areas had an "Innsmouth look"
